occurrenceRemarks: CSBR Slide Grant Image 2016; IZ number 83614; lot count 1; Microslide 01, balsam, leg; other number YPM 4961 or YPM 4962; other number USNM 37753 or USNM 37754; type status comment: The slide is that of a mounted leg. It was originally labeled as "Nymphon macrum Type figured." The "macrum" and type were subsequently crossed out. A review of the USFC distrubution sheets (IZAR No. 1901) showed the figured specimen as YPM 4961/USNM 37753. However, a review of the Pycnogonida ledger showed YPM 4962/USNM 37754 annotaed as a "mounted antenna." It is believed a subsequent cataloger erred in calling it an antenna and it is in fact a mounted leg. A review of the slide shows great similarities to the leg figured in Wilson, 1880, pl. IV, fig. 21 and its believed to have been used by Wilson, and cited in the table on p. 487 as part of the lot 4962. The USFC distribution sheets have the "type" as being USNM 37557, which corresponds to the lot 4965 as cited in Wilsons paper. The "type" designation on the sheets was done post description and in fact all specimens mentioned and figured by Wilson would be considered Syntypes. There is some doubt however as to which lot (4961 or 4962) and locality this slide should be attributed to and should be reexamined by an Pycnogonida expert.
